g.text: It's a specification that provide runtime environment in which java bytecode can executed.
JVM, JRE, JDK are platform dependent, because each Os have different configuration.
JVM are available for software and hardware platform.
There are three notions of the JVM: specification, implementation, and instance.
The JVM performs the following main tasks:
JRE is set of software tools which is use for java application development
It used to provide runtime environment
It's consist of set of library + other files that JVM used at runtime.
Implementation of JRE is actively release by compaines.
JDK contains private JVM (JAVA Virtual Machine) and few other resource like Interperator/Loader (java), Compiler (javac),
an archiver (jar) and document generator (Javadoc) etc. to complete development of java application.
